The paper deals with algorithms for drawing graphs on surfaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithms involve manipulating the combinatorial structure of the graph, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the topological properties of the graphs, such as the existence of fundamental cycles, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper's focus on graph visualization and drawing suggests a connection to information visualization (cs.SI).
